  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA210-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi talaimakaṉai neruṅkic colluvāḷāy vāyil nērntatu (ET: tōḻi nērvāḷ kūṟiyatu).</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante grants the door, being one who speaks directed to HIM.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA210">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            arikāṉ māṟiya vaṅka ṇakalvayaṉ</l>
<l>            maṟukā luḻuta vīrac ceṟuviṉ</l>
<l>            vittoṭu ceṉṟa vaṭṭi paṟpala</l>
<l>            mīṉoṭu peyarum yāṇa rūra</l>
<l>            neṭiya moḻitaluṅ kaṭiya vūrtaluñ </l>
<l>            celva maṉṟutañ ceyviṉaip payaṉē</l>
<l>            cāṉṟōr celva meṉpatu cērntōr</l>
<l>            puṉka ṇañcum paṇpiṉ</l>
<l>            meṉkaṭ celvañ celvameṉ patuvē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O man from the fertile village,</l>
<l rend="indent">where in the wide paddy fields in neat sections<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kaṇ</term> obviously refers here to the sections of the field which are divided by boulders that keep the water (cf. KT 375.3 <term xml:lang="ta">viyaṉ kaṇ irum puṉattu</term>, NA 400.1 <term xml:lang="ta">nel viḷai kaḻaṉi nēr kaṇ ceṟuviṉ</term>).</note>, changed</l>
<l rend="indent">since harvest time,</l>
<l rend="indent">the baskets, that had gone with seed to the wet fields that were ploughed,</l>
<l rend="indent2">at another time come [back] with many many fish,</l>
<l>– talking at length and mounting [your horse] quickly</l>
<l>is not wealth, [wealth is] the yield of the work one does.</l>
<l>What is called wealth by the noble ones</l>
<l>is called the wealth of wealth:</l>
<l rend="indent4">tenderness</l>
<l>of a kind that fears sorrow in those one is close to.<note place="foot">As with most of the sentential poems, syntax and message are ambiguous. Clear, however, is that celvam is used here as a synonym for <term xml:lang="ta">poruḷ</term> - compare the sentential poems KT 174 and NA 16.</note></l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
